Of course if you have mana free stuff, then no pb !<br>
<br>
about hot keys, I, personally, hate them for chain casting. I, also, do not like the button in the pet box, they too slow, too random (i mean the answer time is not sure), then too dangerous. My pet is my life, I don't play randomly with my life.<br>
To avoid typo i used one easy technic :<br>
before sumoning 1st pet I type (slowly if needed !) <br>
/pet get lost<br>
/pet report health<br>
<br>
I sumon pet. <br>
Now with shift upkey, I can call those 2 instructions back, I am sure i won't make any error typing them.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
P.S. of course now I have an epic, chain casting is much more difficult (20 seconds casting !) when I solo, or when I duo with a caster, I very often have a GV memed, then in case of danger I can chain cast ! <br>
<br>
BTW there is another way of 'chain casting' when you are with a mage partner : send pet. partner wait a bit, and send pet. When your pet is at 25% reclaim, and sumon new. Same for your partner. Works rather well. We have on our server a bunch of mages who work together, and the reclaim technic is the best to spare mana, letting pet(s) tank and do 99.99 of the work.<br>
