<br>
Unless you are fighting an extreme magic resistant mob, where the malosi-line of spells do nothing to help the pet to get root to stick, you can let the pet die before you cast the new. This gives you the option of using an extra line in the chain pet macro, so you get<br>
<br>
/cast 1 (summon pet)<br>
/pause XX (depending on the current cast time)<br>
/pet attack<br>
/cast 2 (current BO)<br>
/cast 3 (current DS)<br>
<br>
If the pet isn't dead when you approach the end of the cast, you just mash the get lost button.<br>
<br>
